00:00:02.500 --> 00:00:07.466
-Material design is alive,
and it lives in a world a lot

00:00:07.466 --> 00:00:14.332
like ours, a world that's
responsive, natural, aware,

00:00:14.332 --> 00:00:16.320
and intentional.

00:00:16.320 --> 00:00:19.480
Material design uses responsive
animation to create energy.

00:00:19.480 --> 00:00:23.020
When you take an action,
feedback is immediate,

00:00:23.020 --> 00:00:25.160
and it never keeps you waiting.

00:00:25.160 --> 00:00:28.030
Motion adapts to the distance
an element needs to travel,

00:00:28.030 --> 00:00:30.050
focusing on how fast
something needs to move,

00:00:30.050 --> 00:00:32.870
rather than how long it
should take to get there.

00:00:32.870 --> 00:00:34.680
Motion should feel
natural, moving the way

00:00:34.680 --> 00:00:36.750
things do in the real world.

00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:39.200
Nothing should
instantly start or stop.

00:00:39.200 --> 00:00:41.600
Elements and motion have
momentum and take time

00:00:41.600 --> 00:00:43.800
to speed up and slow down.

00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:45.621
They respond to
forces like gravity,

00:00:45.621 --> 00:00:49.860
moving in curved paths,
instead of in straight lines.

00:00:49.860 --> 00:00:52.942
Material is also aware
of the world around it.

00:00:52.942 --> 00:00:54.400
The way something
enters the screen

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:57.005
can affect the movement
of everything else.

00:00:57.005 --> 00:01:00.900
Elements can push other
elements out of the way,

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:02.126
or attract them.

00:01:02.126 --> 00:01:04.799
Above all, material
isn't random.

00:01:04.799 --> 00:01:07.390
There's a purpose
behind every animation.

00:01:07.390 --> 00:01:08.830
Motion guides you.

00:01:08.830 --> 00:01:10.990
It keeps you focused
on what's important

00:01:10.990 --> 00:01:12.670
and makes sure you
don't get lost.

00:01:12.670 --> 00:01:15.110
It also hints at how
something might react,

00:01:15.110 --> 00:01:17.840
even before it's triggered.

00:01:17.840 --> 00:01:20.040
Whether your brand
is fun and playful,

00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:24.590
or serious and straightforward,
using the motion principles

00:01:24.590 --> 00:01:27.190
for material design can help
you produce a quick, clear,

00:01:27.190 --> 00:01:29.478
and cohesive experience.

00:01:29.478 --> 00:01:32.442
Get to know how things
move at design.google.com.

